  "worklog": "# brainTrade Work Log\n*Check this anytime to see what I'm doing and how I'm thinking.*\n\n---\n\n## 2026-04-21 18:16 UTC \u2014 [P3: Strategy Development] Combined Evening Filter Beats Threshold-Only\n\n**Task:** Test the next strategy-development candidate for the PM bot: combine the stronger evening bias threshold with V5b quality control, instead of treating those as separate ideas.\n**Finding:**\n- Both bots are alive and PM remains flat. The bot is correctly ignoring 18 UTC because it is outside active hours, and live bias remains well below entry threshold.\n- I backtested three evening-strategy variants on the enriched Apr 1+ YES dataset:\n  - **Baseline V5a:** 30 trades, **63.3% WR**, `pnl = 6.729`\n  - **Evening threshold 55 only:** 27 trades, **66.7% WR**, `pnl = 7.788`\n  - **Evening threshold 55 + block weak V5b tags (`REDUCE_MILD_BEAR`, `BOOST`)**: 25 trades, **72.0% WR**, `pnl = 9.788`\n- I also tested a softer version where weak evening tags are half-sized instead of blocked. That still improved results, but less: **effective n = 26.0**, weighted WR **69.2%**, weighted P&L **8.788**.\n- The detail makes sense. The ugly evening cluster is concentrated in exactly the weak-tag bucket:\n  - `2026-04-06 19:05` bias `-62.2`, **LOSS**, `REDUCE_MILD_BEAR`\n  - `2026-04-06 19:10` bias `-56.1`, **LOSS**, `REDUCE_MILD_BEAR`\n  - `2026-04-07 19:35` bias `-53.2`, **LOSS**, `BOOST`\n- That means evening bias tightening helps, but **the real unlock is combining session-specific selectivity with V5b quality gating**.\n\n**My thinking:**\nThis is the first strategy variant that feels like a real upgrade instead of a partial bandage. Threshold-only improves the evening leak, but not enough. V5b already knows which evening setups are structurally sketchy. When I combine those two layers, the bot stops paying tuition on the exact trades that have been hurting us. I like the block version more than half-size because the sample says these are not just lower-conviction trades, they are active drag.\n\n**Decision:**\n- Promote a new leading P3 candidate for live deployment: **keep mornings unchanged, require `|bias| >= 55` at 19h/20h, and block evening trades tagged `REDUCE_MILD_BEAR` or `BOOST`.**\n- This now beats both baseline V5a and the threshold-only tweak on the backtest we have.\n- I am not editing live code in this heartbeat because I want one clean implementation pass, not rushed patching during research.\n\n**Next:** Implement this as a named candidate patch in `trading_bot.py` or a deploy note, with hour-specific threshold logic and evening V5b blocking. Then shadow-validate it against the next active session before full live rollout.\n\n---\n## 2026-04-21 18:01 UTC \u2014 [P2: Smart Entry] Evening Bias Threshold Tightening Backtest\n\n**Task:** Backtest a specific smart-entry tweak on the enriched post-Apr-1 dataset: keep the current morning threshold intact, but require stronger bias in the weaker evening session to reduce low-quality trades.\n**Finding:**\n- Both bots are alive and PM",
